{
  "title": "Beat Bank",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "~450 fixed drum",
        "patterns across 24",
        "genres. No randomness.",
        "",
        "Beat Bank is a MIDI FX",
        "drum sequencer. It",
        "loops the pattern you",
        "pick and plays the",
        "sound generator in the",
        "same slot (e.g. an SF2",
        "drum kit), using GM",
        "drum notes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "How to use",
      "lines": [
        "In a chain slot:",
        " - Sound generator: a",
        "   drum kit (SF2, or a",
        "   sampler like MrDrums",
        "   with a preset kit).",
        " - MIDI FX: Beat Bank.",
        "",
        "Menu: Pattern, Globals,",
        "Swap.",
        "",
        "Pattern opens a grid",
        "view. Genre-first:",
        " - jog: cycle beats in",
        "   the current genre",
        " - knob 1-6: pad/note of",
        "   each row (positional)",
        " - knob 7: swing",
        " - knob 8: switch genre",
        "It shows the grid, the",
        "pad each drum drives,",
        "and which knob edits it.",
        "Click/Back exit. Loops",
        "when Move plays.",
        "",
        "Globals: Swing + Note",
        "Map (also on knob 2 /",
        "in the Pattern view)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Change Pads",
      "lines": [
        "In the Pattern view the",
        "knobs re-point each drum",
        "voice to a different pad",
        "(drumrack) or note (gm),",
        "live while you audition.",
        "",
        "Pad knobs are positional:",
        " K1 = 1st row, K2 = 2nd,",
        " .. up to K6 (6th row).",
        "Rows are in fixed order",
        "(kick, snare, hats, then",
        "extras), so a voice",
        "keeps its pad across",
        "patterns; only which",
        "knob reaches it moves.",
        "(K7 = swing, K8 = genre.)",
        "",
        "Each row shows its knob",
        "number and the pad it",
        "hits. Handy for matching",
        "a MrDrums kit without",
        "leaving Beat Bank. Edits",
        "save with the slot;",
        "switching Note Map",
        "resets them."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Note Map",
      "lines": [
        "Sets which MIDI notes",
        "the drums use:",
        "",
        " gm - full General MIDI",
        "  drum map. Use with",
        "  SF2 / soundfont kits.",
        "",
        " drumrack - all notes",
        "  in 36-51, the Move",
        "  drum-rack range. Use",
        "  with MrDrums and",
        "  other pad samplers.",
        "",
        "Default is drumrack",
        "(most drum synths). Only",
        "switch to gm for SF2.",
        "",
        "Cowbell/Conga/Perc only",
        "sound in drumrack mode",
        "on 36-51 samplers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Recording",
      "lines": [
        "Record the Schwung way:",
        "Shift+Sample (Quantized",
        "Sampler) resamples the",
        "chain's audio to a WAV",
        "in Samples/Schwung/.",
        "",
        "No Move-track mixing -",
        "it stays in Schwung."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Your Own",
      "lines": [
        "Patterns are plain",
        ".beat text files. Drop",
        "your own in:",
        " UserData/schwung/",
        "  beatbank/patterns/",
        "",
        "See _HOWTO.txt there",
        "for the format."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
